{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"745fb760-541a-4eff-9574-594403f3e025","content":"Here's what you need for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT on .NET 11:\n\n**Environment variables** (add to your container spec):\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"            # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"   # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes** — add a volume for dumps and mount it:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      # ... your existing image/command ...\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /dumps\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]   # required by createdump\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi          # adjust to your expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** — `createdump` uses `ptrace` to read process memory; without this capability the dump will fail.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** — essential for NativeAOT since the runtime doesn't bundle `createdump` and won't find it automatically.\n- **`emptyDir`** — dumps are ephemeral; swap for a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- **Dump type 4 (Full)** gives the most detail but produces large files. Use type 1 (Mini) or 3 (Triage) if space is a concern.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8f80cab3-42fb-4cde-ad3a-31201374fb22","outputTokens":602,"requestId":"201B:15632C:7AF193:8DB6AC:69F01230"},"id":"016fb510-e0d6-4f02-bb56-ae37d6480a8e","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:49:52.310Z","parentId":"20717a6d-65f3-43fc-9eea-0cac9a5beb2d"}
